 form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":65,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Alice was born about 1390, in Somerset, England. She married Sir Stephen Pruet about 1414. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1390–":"umbes 1390–Surnud","1387–Male":"1387–Surnud","1415–Male":"1415–Surnud","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1415":"1415","about 1390":"umbes 1390","about 1415":"umbes 1415","1455":"1455","1387":"1387","about 1414":"umbes 1414","1390":"1390","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England"},"fi":{"about 1390–":"noin 1390–Kuollut","1387–Male":"1387–Kuollut","1415–Male":"1415–Kuollut","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1415":"1415","about 1390":"noin 1390","about 1415":"noin 1415","1455":"1455","1387":"1387","about 1414":"noin 1414","1390":"1390","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England"},"fr":{"about 1390–":"environ 1390–Décédée","1387–Male":"1387–Décédé","1415–Male":"1415